Looking at the balance sheet, the "Retained Earnings" line item is specifically what we're looking for. This account captures the accumulated profits that have been kept within the business rather than distributed as dividends.

From the balance sheet:
- Initial Retained Earnings (as of 2023-12-31): 0.00
- End Retained Earnings (as of 2024-01-29): 1163543.07

This shows that the company started the period with no retained earnings and ended with positive retained earnings of 1,163,543.07, meaning the company generated profit during this period that was retained in the business.
